  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To limit human-to-human transmission of COVID-19 among vulnerable populations in Syria through prevention and response activities in the targeted areas.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Contain the spread of the Corona pandemic and provide a comprehensive response to people from the risk of the Corona pandemic, especially the most vulnerable (community, IDPs, returnees, the elderly, persons with disabilities, children at risk of malnutrition, people with chronic diseases, care homes (juveniles). Etc., by providing specialized services to respond to this pandemic, reducing the deterioration of the social situation and livelihoods, enabling teams and work cadres, and equipping health centers and dispensaries with the necessary medical equipment and tools. These activities will be implemented in the following governorates: Damascus countryside, Hama, Aleppo, and Idlib. The overall number of beneficiaries reached /11515/ (direct persons) and /15000/ (indirect persons).
All these areas are with high severity scale from (4 to 6) according to the sector information  

Expected outputs of program implementation:
1- Provide Dignity Kits  To the most vulnerable groups such as returnees, elderly, people with chronic diseases, women heads of households, people with specific needs, and women survived of violence. 

2- Provide Case Management for vulnerable and most vulnerable people (GBV, CM, PSS) to the aforementioned areas. 
3- Provide community-led initiatives There could be initiatives on other topics, depending on the study of needs and available resources in each region.
Note that the SSSD will implement all the proposed activities in areas where SSSD does not have other partners: such as UNHCR
This enables us to cover a wider area</narrative>
  </description>
